        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add catalog taxonomy and author topics",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- add a shared catalog taxonomy with one stored primary category and normalized author topics for skills and plugins\n- wire category/topic metadata through publish, import, public projections, audited moderator corrections, and a resumable dry-run migration\n- add category/topic browse filters and official-first category pagination with community fallback\n- render author topics across catalog cards and document the durable taxonomy contract\n\n## Validation\n\n- `bunx vitest run convex/packages.public.test.ts convex/skills.publicListCursor.test.ts convex/skills.packageCatalog.test.ts convex/httpApiV1.handlers.test.ts`\n- `bun run ci:static`\n- `bun run ci:unit`\n- `bun run ci:types-build`\n- `bun run ci:packages`\n- `bunx convex codegen`\n- `bunx convex insights`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `$autoreview`\n\n## Browser proof\n\n- verified the skills browse sidebar renders all 15 public categories on desktop\n- verified the plugins browse sidebar includes Model & Inference Providers\n- verified the 390x844 mobile filters drawer wraps and exposes all categories without overlap\n\n## Runtime validation note\n\nLocal Convex deployment and the migration dry run are blocked by unrelated pre-existing local development data drift: package release `mn7abx2eb2tks28n9pt9awjqhh862qam` contains `clawScanNote`, which is not accepted by the current `packageReleases` validator. Because the updated functions could not deploy locally, live end-to-end category/topic filtering and official-first pagination were not claimed as browser proof.\n\nA feature-mode `proof:ui` attempt was also infrastructure-blocked before the app ran: Hetzner returned `401 unauthorized` for its configured token, while brokered AWS used Ubuntu 26.04, which Playwright does not support for Chromium. A separate fresh AWS Convex runtime attempt installed dependencies but its local Convex process did not open the requested port. The one-shot AWS leases were released.\n",
        "branch": "codex/catalog-taxonomy-author-topics",
